{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a5406e16-3245-41bc-acfe-983751344d57","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2** / .NET 9.0 — great, that unlocks the modern patterns.\n\nIn MSTest v3, `TestContext` is injected via the **constructor** (no more `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property). Both sync and async init are supported via `[TestInitialize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // TestContext injected via constructor\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // Async init (e.g., DB seeding, HTTP client setup)\n        await SomeAsyncSetup();\n\n        // Sync work is fine here too\n        SomeSyncSetup();\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        await SomeAsyncTeardown();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(true);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points for MSTest 3.x:**\n\n| Pattern | How |\n|---|---|\n| `TestContext` injection | Constructor parameter (preferred over property) |\n| Sync init | `[TestInitialize] public void Init()` |\n| Async init | `[TestInitialize] public async Task InitAsync()` |\n| Per-class (static) init | `[ClassInitialize] public static async Task ClassInit(TestContext ctx)` |\n| Cleanup | Same pattern with `[TestCleanup]` / `[ClassCleanup]` |\n\nThe old property-injection style (`public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }`) still works but constructor injection is the recommended approach in v3.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7d3b3f5a-4201-473f-a705-2a6934db4f2d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection** via constructor (MSTest 3.x supports constructor injection of `TestContext`)\n2. **Sync initialization** via `[TestInitialize]` method\n3. **Async initialization** via `[TestInitialize]` on an `async Task` method (supported in MSTest v2+)\n\nAlso, in MSTest 3.x, you can use `[ClassInitialize]` and `[ClassCleanup]` with lifecycle attributes.\n\n\nNow I'm formulating a concise answer about the best practices for their setup.","outputTokens":630},"id":"7163b84c-d2f0-4cef-86fe-346d4e13b209","timestamp":"2026-04-05T02:00:33.810Z","parentId":"54d2e114-7b23-429f-90a5-0bb8ec6c260a"}
